**DEPLOYMENT GUIDE**
I. Using embedded H2 database
	For local development
		1. Go to application.yml and change profile to 'local'
		2. Go to application-local.yml and change the url:
			url: jdbc:h2:file:~/test; #for Linux, mac os x
			or
			url: jdbc:h2:file:C:/data/test; #for Windows
		3.1 Go to project root folder and run:
			$ mvn clean install
			$ mvn spring-boot:run
		3.2 Or you can use your favorite IDE of choice and config the project as maven project, resolve the dependency, then run the main() class in SwingApplication.class.

II. Using other database engine
	Currently only support MySQL and MariaDB connections. If you want to connect to other database engine, add appropiate connector dependency to pom.xml
		1. Go to application.yml and change profile to 'prod'
		2. Create a CustomDialect class inside root package (com.mycompany.pos)
				---------------------------------------------------------------------
				package com.mycompany.pos;

				import org.hibernate.dialect.MariaDB103Dialect;

				public class CustomDialect extends MariaDB103Dialect {
					public String getTableTypeString() {
						return " ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 DEFAULT COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci";
					}
				}
				---------------------------------------------------------------------
			where 'MariaDB103Dialect' is the syntax dialect of your database engine. Consult https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/orm/5.3/javadocs/org/hibernate/dialect/package-summary.html
			to find the correct dialect and replace. This class is to make sure the your data will be saved in correct UTF-8 charset if you use Vietnamese.
		3. Make sure you already created the database 'java_pos'
		4. Go to application-prod.yml and change the necessary info (url, username & password, dialect)
		5. Do the same as step 3.x in section I

